<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880603-0069 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Barrister Information Systems </HL><SO> </SO><CO> BIS </CO><IN> EDP </IN><TEXT>   Barrister Information Systems Corp., Buffalo, N.Y., said it introduced a desktop publishing system that enables law firms to produce near-typeset-quality documents internally.    Barrister, which supplies computer systems to the legal profession, said the $16,900 system includes a graphics monitor, keyboard with a legal character set, a &quot;mouse&quot; pointing device and graphics printer. The company also is offering a $3,400 optical page scanner that converts handwriting, artwork, photographs and other graphics for use with the system. </TEXT></DOC>